</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E624066FF485AFE120898A2" blockId="15.[151,1437,1007,2005]" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FF485AFE151899EF" bold="true" box="[199,533,1764,1789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Comparisons and Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FDA95AFF15F999EE" authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1962" box="[550,756,1764,1788]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lenimen">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FDA95AFF15F999EE" box="[550,756,1764,1788]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Epigonus lenimen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FC225AFF135B99EE" baseAuthorityName="Giglioli" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[941,1110,1765,1788]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="constanciae">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FC225AFF135B99EE" box="[941,1110,1765,1788]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. constanciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by having a pungent opercular spine (Okamoto 2012). This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FCCD5B1314CF9832" baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[834,962,1800,1824]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FCCD5B1314CF9832" box="[834,962,1800,1824]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having 11 + 14 vertebrae; however, it differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FEA65B3716A79856" baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[297,426,1836,1860]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FEA65B3716A79856" box="[297,426,1836,1860]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in orbital diameter longer than postorbital length (
<figureCitation id="133012AB6E624066FC785B3613469856" box="[1015,1099,1836,1861]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="16.[151,250,701,723]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,267,679]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[188,1398,267,679]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 12. Epigonus lenimen, MNHN 1989-1121, 1 of 2 specimens, 108.6 mm SL." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1182193/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) (vs. orbital diameter shorter than postorbital length in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FE315B4B1533987A" baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[446,574,1872,1896]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FE315B4B1533987A" box="[446,574,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and in lacking two nub-like structures on the symphysis of lower jaw (vs. present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FE9F5B6F169D989E" baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[272,400,1908,1932]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FE9F5B6F169D989E" box="[272,400,1908,1932]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The other 5 species of the group in the 
<collectingRegion id="49CFC0CC6E624066FCFC5B6F14C3989E" box="[883,974,1909,1932]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Western" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Western</collectingRegion>
Indian Ocean, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FBF05B6F121B989E" authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[1151,1302,1908,1932]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FBF05B6F121B989E" box="[1151,1302,1908,1932]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FAA85B6F1279989E" authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[1319,1396,1908,1932]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="idai">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FAA85B6F1279989E" box="[1319,1396,1908,1932]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. idai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FA0B5B6F164B98A2" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marimonticolus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FA0B5B6F164B98A2" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. marimonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FEDB5B8316ED98A2" authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[340,480,1944,1968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FEDB5B8316ED98A2" box="[340,480,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FD9A5B8315B398A2" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[533,702,1944,1968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="waltersensis">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FD9A5B8315B398A2" box="[533,702,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. waltersensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, have 10 + 15 vertebrae (vs. 11 + 
<quantity id="4CF3A3CB6E624066FBB25B82137B98A2" box="[1085,1142,1943,1968]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" unit="in" value="14.0">14 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FBF25B8313F898A2" authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1962" box="[1149,1269,1944,1968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lenimen">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FBF25B8313F898A2" box="[1149,1269,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. lenimen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3115DA56E624079FF485BA715509FC7" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="277" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E624066FF485BA7129198C7" blockId="15.[151,1437,1007,2005]" box="[199,1436,1980,2005]" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FF485BA7169D98C6" authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1962" box="[199,400,1980,2004]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lenimen">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FF485BA7169D98C6" box="[199,400,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Epigonus lenimen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is originally described based on 
<typeStatus id="54B0B08C6E624066FD715BA6146D98C7" box="[766,864,1980,2005]" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">holotype</typeStatus>
and nine 
<typeStatus id="54B0B08C6E624066FC425BA7133598C7" box="[973,1080,1981,2005]" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">paratypes</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F31C4EBE6E624066FBF35BA613EF98C7" box="[1148,1250,1980,2005]" name="Australia" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Australia</collectingCountry>
