</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E7D4079FF185C8D15509FC7" blockId="16.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="277">
According to a re-examination of Whitley’s 
<typeStatus id="54B0B08C6E7D4079FD2C5C8215DE9FA2" box="[675,723,152,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="277">type</typeStatus>
series by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A73DF6E7D4079FCDE5C8214FE9FA2" box="[849,1011,152,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="277" refId="ref20071" refString="Mayer, G. F. (1974) A revision of the cardinalfish genus Epigonus (Perciformes, Apogonidae), with descriptions of two new species. Bulletin Museum of Comparative Zoology, 146, 147 - 203." type="journal article">Mayer (1974)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<typeStatus id="54B0B08C6E7D4079FBBE5C8213919FA2" box="[1073,1180,152,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="277">paratypes</typeStatus>
